# Enterprise MVP Foundation Blueprint

## Purpose

This blueprint defines the default foundation for VibOS Comp missions. The product scope may be small, but the engineering foundation must be strong enough for a senior engineer, security reviewer, enterprise design partner, or competition judge to inspect without finding obvious omissions.

## Readiness Thresholds

| Threshold | Use Case | Standard |
|---|---|---|
| Local proof | Private demo, no real users, no real sensitive data | Must be runnable, testable, and honest about missing production controls |
| Design-partner MVP | External design partner, pilot, judge review, or investor technical diligence | Must include the full foundation baseline unless explicitly and safely scoped out |
| Production-ready | Real customers, real revenue, regulated data, or operational dependency | Must pass full gates, harden operations, and document incident/rollback paths |

## Non-Negotiable Rule

Cut features first. Do not cut security, observability, test evidence, dependency intelligence, dependency freshness, deployment hygiene, or clear ownership boundaries to make the MVP look larger.

## Foundation Domains

Use `.vibeos/reference/comp/enterprise-mvp-foundation.json` as the machine-readable source of truth. Every requirement maps to:

- a verification evidence type
- one or more gates or audits where available
- a scorecard field for later judging
- a deferral rule that states when it may be skipped

## Required Domains

- Identity and access
- Data integrity
- Flow integrity and objective fidelity
- System invariants and state safety
- Security and abuse resistance
- Configuration and secrets
- Testing and verification
- Observability and operations
- Delivery infrastructure, CI/CD, deployment, and release hygiene
- Frontend experience quality
- Performance and scalability
- Dependencies, supply chain, and current-source dependency intelligence
- Documentation and evidence

## Stack Variants

Use stack variants as implementation guidance, not mandatory framework choices:

- `.vibeos/reference/comp/stack-typescript-node.json`
- `.vibeos/reference/comp/stack-python-fastapi.json`
- `.vibeos/reference/comp/stack-frontend-app.json`
- `.vibeos/reference/comp/stack-dependency-currency.json`

When stack choices are made, verify current framework/library docs before creating WOs or installing dependencies, then capture runtime compatibility, lockfile, security audit, and upgrade-path evidence.
